      <h2>Bosch washer repair — common questions</h2>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>E02 / E03 door lock codes</summary>
        <p>Test lock resistance 159-211 ohms. Outside range = replacement $195-$285. Try 5-min power cycle first (10% of codes clear on reset). Emergency release tab near drain pump filter if clothes trapped.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>E13 / E18 / E23 drainage codes</summary>
        <p>E13 = pump timeout OR door lock. E18 = hose too high (max 39"). E23 = water in base pan. Clean filter first — 70% resolve free. Drain pump replacement $165-$245.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Violent shaking during spin</summary>
        <p>Check shipping bolts first (if recently moved). Unbalanced load (redistribute). Shock absorber set worn year 8-10 — $385-$540 4-piece set replacement (not individual).</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>300 vs 500 vs 800 Series</summary>
        <p>Same chassis. 300 = basic, 1200-1400 RPM. 500 = WAT prefix, 1400 RPM, more cycles. 800 = WAW prefix, 1400-1600 RPM, EcoSilence direct-drive motor (no F21 brush failures).</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>F21 motor brush failure</summary>
        <p>300/500 Series only (800 Series brushless). Year 6-8 typical. $165-$245 replacement extends motor to year 12-15. Much cheaper than $585-$785 full motor replacement.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>Bosch vs Miele compact washer</summary>
        <p>Miele = 2x price, 10-year motor/drum warranty, better long-term if staying 8+ years. Bosch 800 = better value for 4-6 year stay or rental. Both fit 24" closets. Both serviced.</p>
      </details>

      <details class="faq">
        <summary>How much does Bosch washer repair cost?</summary>
